{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"262o","heading":"Negotiations concerning replenishment or increase in capital; annual reports on implementation of lending policy goals","label":"262o Negotiations concerning replenishment or increase in capital; annual reports on implementation of lending policy goals","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/ch7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Codificationis based on section 701 of title VII of H.R. 3750, One Hundredth Congress, as introduced , and enacted into law by .Section 1501 of Pub. L. 95–118Pub. L. 100–202Dec. 11, 1987","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsThe definitions in apply to this section.section 262p–5 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The establishment of a unified program within each multilateral development bank to assess the extent to which bank lending benefits the least advantaged members of society, particularly women and the poor, and to increase the extent to which such members benefit from future bank lending.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide in-country liaison services for nongovernmental organizations operating at the community level;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"monitor the impact of project and nonproject lending on local populations; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensure compliance with loan conditionalities, especially loan conditionalities relating to the protection of the quality of life of the poor and the rights of aboriginal minorities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"recruitment of additional permanent professional staff; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"training programs for existing staff members in these subject areas.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"With respect to the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development, the establishment of a program for policy-based lending to promote the sustainable use of renewable resources and the protection of the environment in borrowing countries.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An increase in the length of any review period established by any multilateral development bank for board review of staff recommendations by such time as would be sufficient to allow the governments of member countries to review and comment on the staff recommendations before any action is taken by the board of directors of such bank on the recommendations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Benefit to the poor.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Involvement of nongovernmental organizations and local and indigenous populations in loan design, implementation, planning, and monitoring.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Integration of, consideration of, and concern for environmental quality and the sustainable use of natural resources into loan design, implementation, planning, and monitoring.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s262o/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs262o%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Recognition of and support for the economic and social development of women.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
